title: Introduction to Programming
description: Learn fundamental programming concepts using Python. Covers variables, loops, functions, and basic data structures.

title: Discrete Mathematics with Applications I
description: Introduction to logic, sets, functions, and proof techniques. Essential for theoretical computer science.

title: Principles of Programming
description: Advanced programming concepts including recursion, data structures, and algorithm analysis using functional programming.

title: Linear Algebra
description: Covers vector spaces, matrices, linear transformations, and eigenvalues. Essential for engineering applications.

title: Mathematical Probability
description: Introduction to probability theory including random variables, distributions, and expectation.

title: Calculus for Science II
description: Continuation of calculus covering techniques of integration, sequences, and series.

title: Introduction to Business
description: Overview of business fundamentals including management, marketing, finance, and operations.

title: Introduction to Marketing
description: Explores marketing principles, consumer behavior, branding, and digital marketing strategies.

title: Introduction to Finance
description: Fundamentals of corporate finance, time value of money, and investment analysis.

title: Engineering Profession and Practice
description: Introduction to engineering design process, ethics, teamwork, and professional practice.

title: Engineering and Entrepreneurship
description: Project-based course teaching design thinking, prototyping, and entrepreneurial mindset.

title: Engineering Design and Graphics
description: Computer-aided design (CAD) fundamentals and technical drawing for engineering applications.

title: Cellular and Molecular Biology
description: Introduction to cell structure, metabolism, genetics, and molecular biology.

title: Biodiversity Evolution Ecology
description: Explores evolution, ecology, and diversity of life from microorganisms to ecosystems.

title: Structure and Bonding
description: Chemical bonding, molecular structure, thermodynamics, and kinetics.

title: Introductory Physics I
description: Classical mechanics including kinematics, dynamics, energy, and momentum.

title: Classical Mythology
description: Explores Greek and Roman myths and their influence on Western culture and literature.

title: Introduction to Philosophy
description: Survey of major philosophical questions including ethics, knowledge, reality, and free will.

title: Ethics and the Good Life
description: Exploration of ethical theories and their application to contemporary moral issues.

title: Introduction to Psychology
description: Overview of psychological science including cognition, development, social behavior, and mental health.

title: Introduction to Sociology
description: Examines social structures, culture, inequality, and social change in contemporary society.

title: Macroeconomic Policy
description: Introduction to macroeconomics including GDP, inflation, unemployment, and fiscal policy.

title: Microeconomic Theory
description: Study of individual decision-making, market structures, and resource allocation.

title: Digital Systems
description: Introduction to digital logic, combinational and sequential circuits, and microprocessors.

title: Materials Science and Engineering
description: Properties and applications of materials including metals, polymers, ceramics, and composites.

title: TestCourse
description: This is a test.
